The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Suri, July 19: A 109-year-old bridge across the Brahmmoni river at Nalhati, which the Darjeeling Mail went through every day, has been closed to passenger trains because it is leaning on one side.

 The railways said a specialist North-East Frontier Railway team has begun the repair job. Till the work is completed, the mail, Uttarbanga Express and other trains will make a detour.

 Ranigunge: Workers of two Ranigunge mines ? North Searsole and Kumardihi ? had to be evacuated on Wednesday. Following days of incessant rain, water had started seeping in.

 Burdwan: Ramena Khatun, a Class IX student of a Burdwan school set herself on fire on Tuesday night apparently after being punished by a teacher for not being attentive in class. She died on Wednesday.




